5000|$|According to chronicler João <b>de</b> Barros, <b>Pêro</b> <b>de</b> Anaia {{was the son}} of Castilian nobleman Diego de Anaya, {{who fought}} in the Castilian civil war of the 1470s for the Beltraneja party, {{alongside}} King Afonso V of Portugal. [...] He moved or was exiled to Portugal at the conclusion of that war. His son <b>Pêro</b> <b>de</b> Anaia became a knight of the Portuguese king's household.|$|R
