50|$|Mid-February, 1505 - The 6th Armada makes {{a stop in}} Mozambique Island for {{repair and}} re-supply. Realizing {{it is going to}} be a two-week stay, Lopo Soares dispatches two ships - <b>Pêro</b> <b>de</b> Mendonça and Lopo de Abreu - ahead of him to Lisbon to {{announce}} the results. <b>Pêro</b> <b>de</b> Mendonça's ship will be lost somewhere after Cape Correntes, probably capsized on the South African coast, and will never be heard from again. Lopo de Abreu will arrive in Lisbon in mid-July.|$|R
