5000|$|Pedro, or Pêro da Covilhã or ( [...] ; c. 1460 [...] - [...] after 1526), {{sometimes}} written: <b>Pero</b> <b>de</b> Covilhăo, was a Portuguese diplomat and explorer.|$|R
50|$|The foundering of <b>Pêro</b> <b>de</b> Anaia's Sant'Iago (sometimes {{referred}} to as the Nunciá) in the Tagus harbour upon departure, prompted the immediate assembly of another six-ship fleet that set out a month later. Although it never caught up with Almeida's fleet, it is sometimes considered part of it. <b>Pêro</b> <b>de</b> Anaia was responsible for erecting a fortress in Sofala, and then, retaining two ships for a local patrol, to send the remaining four on to India to place themselves under D. Francisco de Almeida.|$|R
